					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5585680#post-3808171</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5585680/scp-2651#post-3808171</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 22 May 2018 01:42:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Nederbird</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2854162</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I vaguely remember reading an earlier version of this a good while ago, but it never left much of an impression on me. This, however, did. I like how you expand upon Ortothan history and religion by showing ancient alien adherents (and without any annoying &quot;guiding humanity&quot; nonsense to boot!), and I like the creative liberties you took with the alien ghosts. While vaguely reminiscent of Yithians (mostly because of the conical body plan), it still feels quite original. An the little Sarkic reference is nice to. ^^</p> <p>More worldbuilding, more food for thought, bizarrely packaged, mighty good read! +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
